l_main_2525676\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104agp1665702896114.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/agp1665702896114.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/agp1665702896114.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"agp1665702896114\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Deploy Stored Procedure Components\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"agp1665702896114__li_d18608e1_d18609e1_d18610e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Edit the $SSP path in the appropriate assignment file to point to the location of your stored procedure components. You must explicitly map the $SSP path, because it has no default mapping.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"agp1665702896114__li_d18611e1_d18612e1_d18613e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If a component has multiple implementations (including a stored procedure component which is not set to default), use the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ujx1665702543107.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujx1665702543107.html\" title=\"Use the [SERVICES_EXEC] section of the assignment file to direct the execution of service components to a network path, COM, or SOAP connector, and to redefine the behavior of COM and SOAP connectors for specific components.\">[SERVICES_EXEC]</a> section to explicitly assign the component to a DBMS connection.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"agp1665702896114__li_d18614e1_d18615e1_d18616e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Review transaction control within your application. By default, DBMS transaction control is not affected by the execution of a stored procedure. However, if transaction control is manipulated within a stored procedure, Uniface cannot guarantee a correct transaction state.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"agp1665702896114__note_w1231ab1b5b1b5b3b1_w1232ab1b5b1b5b3_w1233ab1b5b1b5_w1234ab1b5b1_w1235ab1b5_w1236ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Multiple (parallel) transactions are supported. A stored procedure runs in the same transaction as the calling Uniface component.</div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"example\" id=\"agp1665702896114__example_fw5_45p_pcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d918554e88\">Example: Mapping Stored Procedure Components to a Connection</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">All stored procedure components are mapped to the $ORA2 (via $SSP)\n               connection, with the exeption of component_1, which is mapped to the $ORA1\n               connection.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"agp1665702896114__pre_sjn_p5p_pcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$ORA1 =ORA:|scott|tiger\n$ORA2 =ORA:|system|manager\n$SSP =$ORA2\n[SERVICES_EXEC]\ncomponent_1 = $ORA1:component_1\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yqa1665702772542.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Naming Specifications for Service Store Procedures</a><p>For Service Stored Procedures, the signature of the Stored Procedure Component maps the names of Uniface components, operations, and parameters to the name of a package, procedure, and parameter names in the procedure.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525676\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525676\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Deploy Stored Procedure Components Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Deploy Stored Procedure Components Edit the $SSP path in the appropriate assignment file to point to the location of your stored procedure components. You must explicitly map the $SSP path, because it has no default mapping. If a component has multiple implementations (including a stored procedure component which is not set to default), use the [SERVICES_EXEC] section to explicitly assign the component to a DBMS connection. Review transaction control within your application. By default, DBMS transaction control is not affected by the execution of a stored procedure. However, if transaction control is manipulated within a stored procedure, Uniface cannot guarantee a correct transaction state. Note: Multiple (parallel) transactions are supported. A stored procedure runs in the same transaction as the calling Uniface component. Example: Mapping Stored Procedure Components to a Connection All stored procedure components are mapped to the $ORA2 (via $SSP) connection, with the exeption of component_1, which is mapped to the $ORA1 connection. [PATHS] $ORA1 =ORA:|scott|tiger $ORA2 =ORA:|system|manager $SSP =$ORA2 [SERVICES_EXEC] component_1 = $ORA1:component_1 Copy Related Links Naming Specifications for Service Store Procedures For Service Stored Procedures, the signature of the Stored Procedure Component maps the names of Uniface components, operations, and parameters to the name of a package, procedure, and parameter names in the procedure. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}